762 Die of Cholera and Meningitis in Tanzania 
A total of 762 people have died of cholera and meningitis in various
parts of Tanzania since January.
Among them 748 of the deaths were caused by cholera out of 14,661
people who contracted the disease, Principal Secretary in the Ministry
of Health Ray Mrope said here today.
Besides, nineteen people were killed out of 136 who had been attacked
by meningitis, he added.
Mrope mentioned the regions which have been hit by cholera as Coast,
Kilimanjaro, Tanga, Dodoma, Mtwara, Lindi, Dar es Salaam and Morogor in
the country.
